e. The aim of this volume is to examine this claim, and to place it in the wider context of recent epistemological debates about the role of sociality in knowledge acquisition, in virtue and social epistemology, and in philosophy and sociology of science.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aSozialphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh1 aBAUMANN, CAROLINE M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFallis, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHakli, Raul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathiesen, Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmid, Hans Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmid, Hans Bernhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSirtes, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSirtes, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTollefsen, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuomela, Raimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Marcel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Marcel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZiv, Anita Konzelmann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitl